# Repo Core

- Keep proposed changes scoped to the area asked in the task.
- Respect the frontend/backend boundary: updates to `frontend/` stay under that directory and backend work stays under `backend/`.
- Use the repo's existing TypeScript configuration and naming conventions unless a strong reason exists to diverge.
- Add tests or update existing ones when modifying behavior that already has coverage.
- Keep documentation (README/SETUP) aligned with any new setup or scripts.
